messages.content: What is the purpose of the ComfyUI-PreviewSubselection-Node?
The ComfyUI-PreviewSubselection-Node is a custom node in ComfyUI that allows users to preview a subselection of images from a larger set of generated images.
How does the ComfyUI-PreviewSubselection-Node display the subselection of images?
Based on the provided images, the ComfyUI-PreviewSubselection-Node displays the subselection of images in a grid format within the ComfyUI interface.
What type of images can be previewed using the ComfyUI-PreviewSubselection-Node?
The ComfyUI-PreviewSubselection-Node can be used to preview any type of images generated within the ComfyUI application, as long as they are part of a larger set of images.
Does the ComfyUI-PreviewSubselection-Node allow users to select specific images from the subselection?
The provided information does not specify whether users can select specific images from the subselection using the ComfyUI-PreviewSubselection-Node.
Is the ComfyUI-PreviewSubselection-Node a built-in feature of ComfyUI?
No, the ComfyUI-PreviewSubselection-Node is a custom node, which means it is an extension or plugin that adds functionality to ComfyUI.
Can the ComfyUI-PreviewSubselection-Node be used to generate new images?
The provided information does not indicate that the ComfyUI-PreviewSubselection-Node can be used to generate new images. Its main purpose is to preview a subselection of already generated images.
Is the ComfyUI-PreviewSubselection-Node compatible with other custom nodes in ComfyUI?
The provided information does not specify whether the ComfyUI-PreviewSubselection-Node is compatible with other custom nodes in ComfyUI.
